## 7. Dockerized run

You already have the `Dockerfile` from the previous answer; with `.env` now added, you can run it containerized.

### 7.1. Build the image

From repo root:

```bash
docker build -t tap919-middleman:dev .
```

This follows typical FastAPI + Docker guidance: copy app, install requirements, run uvicorn. [seenode](https://seenode.com/blog/deploy-fastapi-docker-and-uvicorn)

### 7.2. Run locally with SQLite

```bash
docker run --rm -p 8000:8000 \
  --env-file .env \
  tap919-middleman:dev
```

- The container reads `.env` for `DATABASE_URL` and `OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT`.
- Same URLs as local dev: `http://localhost:8000/docs`, `/internal/ping`, etc.

If you later switch to Postgres, just change `DATABASE_URL` in `.env` to point to your DB service.

